Wash and dry produce.

Trim ends from @zucchini{1} and @carrots{6%ounce}; peel carrot. Using a #peeler{}, shave zucchini and carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy cores; discard cores.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss veggie ribbons with @ponzu sauce{18%milliliters}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Set aside to marinate, stirring occasionally.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; finely chop whites. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb} until you have ½ tsp. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a second medium bowl, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the scallion greens, remaining ponzu, @veggie pho stock concentrate{1}, @water{3%tbsp}, @sugar{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Form into 6 equal-size meatballs.

> For 4 servings, use two veggie pho stock concentrates, 6 TBSP water, 1¼ tsp sugar, and ½ tsp salt instead.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-6%minutes}. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches.) Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out any burnt bits in pot if needed.

Return same pot to medium-high heat. (TIP: If pan seems dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Add ginger and scallion whites; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @water{4%cups}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, and remaining @veggie pho stock concentrate{2}; bring to a boil.

Once broth begins to boil, add meatballs along with any juices from plate. Reduce heat to a low simmer and cover. Cook until flavors meld, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide zucchini and carrot ribbons between #bowls{}; top with meatballs and as much broth as you like. Top with scallion greens, a big squeeze of lime juice, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.